<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_ærtajun" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><form type="lemma"><orth>ærtajun</orth><form type="inflected" subtype="ptcp"><orth>ærtad</orth></form></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>купать</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>bathe</q></cit></sense><re xml:lang="os-x-iron"><lang/><form type="lemma"><orth>najyn</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>id.</q></cit><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>id.</q></cit><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/></sense></re><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>kud ǧæwuj хе ærtajun</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>как нужно купаться</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>how one need to take a bath</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_FS"/><biblScope>II 83</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>bon ku isæntæf wa, wædta nахе særtajʒinan</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>когда день станет знойным, мы выкупаемся</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>when it becomes sultry, we will take a bath</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_FS"/><biblScope>II 81</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>Narti Acæmæz sæwmon wazali æ bæx nirtajgæj ... rafændarast uj „</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>Нарт Ацамаз, выкупав коня в утренней прохладе, отправляется в путь</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>having bathed a horse in the cool of the morning, Nart Acamaz starts on his journey</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>58%l156—158%l</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>kud ǧæwuj хе ærtajun</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>как нужно купаться</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>how one need to take a bath</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_FS"/><biblScope>II 83</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>bon ku isæntæf wa, wædta nахе særtajʒinan</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>когда день станет знойным, мы выкупаемся</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>when it becomes sultry, we will take a bath</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_FS"/><biblScope>II 81</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>Narti Acæmæz sæwmon wazali æ bæx nirtajgæj ... rafændarast uj „</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>Нарт Ацамаз, выкупав коня в утренней прохладе, отправляется в путь</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>having bathed a horse in the cool of the morning, Nart Acamaz starts on his journey</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>58%l156—158%l</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Сращение преверба %iær%i- с глаголом %itajun%i [см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tajyn"/>], бытующим в значении ‘таять’. В сращении с другими превербами (%iū%i- | %io%i-, %ifæl%i-) этот же глагол наличен в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ūdajyn"/> | %iodajun%i и д. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fældajun"/> ‘мочить’, ‘увлажнять’. Возможно, однако, и возведение к *%iϑrā%i-; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="oru"><lang/><w>tr-</w><gloss><q>пить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prc"><lang/><w>ter-</w><gloss><q>пить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>tar</w><gloss><q>влажный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>ttre</w><gloss><q>капля</q></gloss></mentioned> (ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærtax"/>).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>24, 119, 362</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">The fusion of the preverb %iær%i- with the verb %itajun%i [see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tajyn"/>], being in use in the meaning ‘to melt’. The fusion with another preverbs (%iū%i- | %io%i-, %ifæl%i-) gives <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ūdajyn"/> | %iodajun%i and Digor <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fældajun"/> ‘to wet’, ‘to moisten’ with the same verb root. It is however possible to trace the word back to *%iϑrā%i-; compare <mentioned xml:lang="oru"><lang/><w>tr-</w><gloss><q>to drink</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prc"><lang/><w>ter-</w><gloss><q>to drink</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>tar</w><gloss><q>wet</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>ttre</w><gloss><q>drop</q></gloss></mentioned> (ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærtax"/>).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>24, 119, 362</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>